James Henry Porteous Oakes (1821 – 1901) was a British Conservative politician.
James was the son of Henry Oakes and Maria Ann Porteus.Oakes was elected Conservative MP for Bury St Edmunds at a by-election in 1852—caused by the appointment of John Stuart as a Vice-Chancellor in the Court of Chancery—and held the seat until 1857 when he was defeated.

response: * James Oakes (historian) (born 1953), professor of history at the City University of New York
* James Oakes (diarist) (1741–1829), diarist, businessman and banker, Bury St Edmunds, Suffolk
